events.name: I/O Extended 2018 MANAMA (FLUTTER)
events.description:
Flutter is Google's mobile SDK for crafting high-quality native interfaces on iOS and Android in record time. Flutter works with existing code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is free and open source.

In our Google IO Extended Flutter codelab, you'll create a simple Flutter app. If you are familiar with object-oriented code and basic programming concepts such as variables, loops, and conditionals, you can complete this codelab. You don't need previous experience with Dart or mobile programming.

A Charged Laptop

events.name: Self-Driving Cars! With Computer Vision and AI

venue.name: Brinc Batelco IoT Hub, Batelco Building

events.description:
Abstract:
Self-driving car is a vehicle that is capable of sensing its environment and navigating without human input. Autonomous cars combine a variety of techniques to perceive their surroundings, including radar, laser light, GPS and computer vision. In this Workshop we will focus on Computer vision. Which is a subset of AI field that deals with how computers can be made for gaining high-level understanding from digital images or videos. In this workshop the attendees will discover a cutting edge technology that scientist will use it in Self-Driving Car technology.

Language:
Arabic with English support where necessary =)

Vision:
• Apply Machine learning concept in an Fun Application. ➢ Learn The basics for AI and Deep learning.

Output:
• Train and Test an simulation on self driving car using Deep learning and Tensorflow.

Workshop Plan :
10:15 – 10:30: Introduction AI and Machine learning
10:30 – 11:00: Programming language syntax
11:00 – 12:00: Neural Network and CNN
1:00 – 1:30: Self-Driving Car simulation Environment.
1:30 – 2:00: Building the Project

events.name: Building Digital Skills of The Future
events.description:
Join Google Developer Group Manama and its speakers for an interesting informal discussion on what the digital skills of the future are and how to best upskill talent.

Their casual panel represents a range of perspectives across AI, Gaming, Digital Agencies and Data Science, each with their own insights into where the current job trends are heading, what are the recommendations on upskilling and the possible barriers to adoption of those specific technologies. events.name: Google I/O Extended 2019 Manama [Machine learning]
events.description:
I/O stands for input/output, as well as the slogan "Innovation in the Open", and that is the title of a large annual developer conference held by Google in Mountain View, California (USA). I/O brings together developers from around the globe for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and a first look at Google’s latest developer products.

I/O Extended events help developers from around the world take part in the I/O experience. In 2018, developers hosted over 500 extended viewing parties and many more joined online, including 3 extended events in Bahrain.

This year we will summarize all the journey in one event presented by Mohammed Buallay, a member of GDG Manama who will attend I/O 2019 in Mountain View, California.
